Feature: Navigation menu
 While holding a presentation a speaker may want move to a specific slide of the presentation or jump to a previous or upcoming presenta-tion. The navigation menu contains the slides of the current presenta-tion, structured through topics and subtopics and entries pointing to the previous and upcoming presentation. The entries of the menu can be selected with the keyboard
  Scenario: Move the selection upwards
  Scenario: Move the selection downwards
  Scenario: Move the selection up one level
  Scenario: Move the selection down one level
  Scenario: Jump to the selected menu entry
